    "body": "In the following code, if I only specified a png format, then I got a figure with a nice tight bounding box. \r\nBut when I also ask for a `ps`, then the png file has NO tight bounding box. \r\n\r\n\r\n`gmt basemap -R0/9/0/5 -Jx1c -Bf1a2 -Bx+lDistance -By+l\"No of samples\" -BWeSn -png,ps linear`\r\n\r\n\r\n![linear](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/173268890-a221cf3b-4aff-483c-9ece-f32416d2d704.png)\r\n\r\n",
